Let me be clear about his, if you feel for some reason you are a &quot;protected class&quot;, you deserve to be treated differently, or you somehow gain a magical right to not be offended by what people say because of your sexual orientation people have the right to criticize you.  And not respect you afterwards.<br>
<br>
I'll get flamed for this, but honestly, what the fuck difference does it make if you are gay or not.  Who cares?  It doesn't give you special rights, it shouldn't make people have to watch what they say around you because they might offend you.  You haven't come right out and said it, but the tone of your posts is that you feel you are oppressed by a culture that uses the same word to describe homosexuals that it occassionally uses to describe something stupid.  It's a ridiculous argument to begin with.  If someone wants to call me cracker ass motherfucker whitey it honestly wouldn't bother me.  They are just words.  They aren't inherantly evil... and even if they are used in a derogatory manner, which I don't think this necessarily was, it's not worth getting worked up over (even though you say you didn't, it's pretty obvious you did), in my opinion.   <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Funny how it turns out that most of the people defending the usage of the term &quot;gay&quot; as &quot;dumb&quot; are themselves str8.<br>
